H0.text: Which motorcycle company introduced the Jet Ski in 1972. Yamaha

H1.text: Which motorcycle company introduced the Jet Ski in 1972. Honda

H2.text: Which motorcycle company introduced the Jet Ski in 1972. Suzuki

H3.text: Which motorcycle company introduced the Jet Ski in 1972. Kawasaki

A4.text: Jet Ski is the brand name of a personal watercraft (PWC) manufactured by Kawasaki, a Japanese company.

A5.text: Released in 1972, the stand-up Kawasaki Jet Ski was the first commercially successful personal watercraft in America (after reaching a license agreement with the inventor of the Sea-Doo, Clayton Jacobson II when his license agreement with Bombardier expired).
